      public Crop()

    • Crop

      public Crop(String farmName, String farmLocation, int cropID, String cropName, int quantityAvailable, String harvestDate, boolean inSeason, String sheetName, String sheetID)
      Constructor for the Crop Object. Sets the Crop object with all the appropriate values (from or to the database).
      Parameters:
      farmName - What farm is the Crop under.
      farmLocation - Where said farm is located.
      cropID - A unique identifier for this specific Crop.
      cropName - The name of the Crop.
      quantityAvailable - How many of the crop is currently on hand.
      harvestDate - When the Crop was harvested (presented in a format valid for Google Sheets)
      inSeason - A boolean that indicates whether the Crop is currently in season.
      sheetName - What Google Sheet the Crop is under.
      sheetID - The numeric identifier for the Google Sheet (Ex: 0 = Sheet1, 1 = Sheet2, etc.). Used as a backup to sheetName in the event that sheetName changes.

  • Method Details

    • getCropID

      public int getCropID()
      Returns to the user what the ID of the Crop is. This is typically used for database access.
      Returns:
      cropID the Crops identifier within the database.

    • getSheetName

      public String getSheetName()
      Returns to the user what sheet the Crop is under. This is quicker than sheetID, but more prone to failure as sheetName can change, while sheetID can't.
      Returns:
      sheetName the sheet that Crop is under.

    • getSheetID

      public String getSheetID()
      Returns the SheetID for the given Crop. Should be used as a backup in the event sheetName is unavailable.
      Returns:
      sheetID the ID of sheetName

    • getCropName

      public String getCropName()
      Returns the name of the Crop object.
      Returns:
      cropName the name of the Crop object.

      Returns:
      quantityAvailable How many of said Crop is available currently.

    • getCropChanges

      public int getCropChanges()
      Returns the current position of the Crop in relation to the database. 0 indicates that no change has happened compared to the database. 1 indicates that the crop has just been created, but not in the database. 2 indicates that the crop has been modified from its database form (but not pushed). 3 indicates that the crop has been deleted, but not changed in the database yet.
      Returns:
      cropChanges The current relation to the database.

    • getHarvestDate

      public String getHarvestDate()
      Returns the harvest date for the Crop. Will be in the format that best suits sheets.v4.*
      Returns:
      harvestDate When the Crop was harvested.

    • isInSeason

      public boolean isInSeason()
      Returns whether the current Crop is in season.
      Returns:
      inSeason Whether the Crop is currently being harvested.

    • setCropChanges

      public void setCropChanges(int cropChanges)
      Method to set whether the crop has been modified for not. 0 indicates that no change has happened compared to the database. 1 indicates that the crop has just been created, but not in the database. 2 indicates that the crop has been modified from its database form (but not pushed). 3 indicates that the crop has been deleted, but not changed in the database yet.
      Parameters:
      cropChanges - Sets the condition of the Crop object in relation to the database.
